  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DPI STRENGTHENING DEMOCRACY BUILDING MEASURES ACROSS TURKEY</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DPI is a neutral, non-partisan INGO working on dialogue facilitation around the Kurdish issue in Turkey. DPI selects participants from across Turkish civil society and politics and provides thematic expertise and guidance to develop models for wider public involvement in promoting peace (&#x2018;Strengthening Democracy Building Measures across Turkey&#x2019; (DMAT) programme). DPI has facilitated a high number of inward visits, while regular on-the-ground briefing materials are also sent to DFA which provide useful contextual information to relevant Units. Lessons-learned from the Northern Ireland Peace Process are complemented by other DPI comparative study visits to South Africa, the Philippines, Colombia and Spain.</narrative>
  </description>
